01/09/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov announced on Tuesday (31 August) that 2,322 more tanks and pieces of Soviet-era military equipment would be destroyed, in line with international conventions. The Bulgarian firm Makmetal was selected to oversee the project through a tender conducted by the ministry. 
In other news, it appears most political parties support the idea of holding the next parliamentary election in June or July of 2005. The opposition initially proposed the idea. (Sega, 24 Chasa - 01/09/04; Mediapool - 31/08/04) 
